com.complexible.common.memory.buffer

Class MemoryLongByteBuffer

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.complexible.common.memory.buffer.AbstractLongByteBuffer
      • com.complexible.common.memory.buffer.MemoryLongByteBuffer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Disposable, LongByteBuffer

    public final class MemoryLongByteBuffer
extends AbstractLongByteBuffer

    Implementation of a LongByteBuffer which is backed by a byte array in memory. Somewhat at odds with the goal of LongByteBuffer since it cannot hold more than a Integer.MAX_VALUE number of bytes, but it's the best strategy for a memory based buffer.

    Since:
    2.1
    Version:
    2.1
    Author:
    Michael Grove
